.TH "stop_two_cpus" 9 "stop_two_cpus" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
stop_two_cpus \- stops two cpus
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" stop_two_cpus
.BI "(unsigned int cpu1 "  ","
.BI "unsigned int cpu2 "  ","
.BI "cpu_stop_fn_t fn "  ","
.BI "void *arg "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cpu1" 12
the cpu to stop
.IP "cpu2" 12
the other cpu to stop
.IP "fn" 12
function to execute
.IP "arg" 12
argument to \fIfn\fP
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Stops both the current and specified CPU and runs \fIfn\fP on one of them.

returns when both are completed.
